President Muhmmadu Buhari has revealed that the Warri to Central Ajaokuta standard gauge railway would be extended from Itakpe to Abuja and from Warri town to Warri port. The President who made this known during a recent broadcast to commemorate 2020 celebration of Democracy Day marking 21 years of uninterrupted civi administration in the country, promised to extend and upgrade railway network with introduction of more locomotives, coaches and wagons for the Abuja- Kaduna Rail Line. While reiterating that the Central Ajaokuta -Itakpe Warri Line has been completed, he said the Lagos-lbadan Rail Line is 90 percent completed and would be extended to the Lagos Port which would help address the long-standing grid-lock at the Apapa port. According to him, the Kano-Maradi Single Track Standard Gauge Railway Coastal Railway Project and Port Harcourt- Maiduguri Standard Gauge Railway, with its associated branch lines running through the South Eastern and Gombe States, industrial park and Bonny Deep Sea Port are all ready for concessioning. The president pointed out that Agriculture remains the key to economic diversification strategy as the Presidential Fertilizer Initiative programme continues to deliver significant quantities of affordable and high-quality fertilizers to our farmers. He said the initiative has also revived 31 blending plants and created a significant number of direct and indirect jobs across the value chain Buhari noted that his government is also revamping the cotton, textile and garment sector via a CBN Textile Revival Intervention Fund that would considerably reduce foreign exchange spent on cotton and other textile imports.